==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hummel
<hw>Hum"mel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Hamble</er>.]</ety> <def>To separate from the awns; -- said of
barley.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hummel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hummel
<hw>Hum"mel</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having no awns or no horns; <as>as,
<ex>hummel</ex>corn; a <ex>hummel</ex> cow.</as></def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hummeler</ent>⟦br⟧
